---
import StaticPageLayout from "@/infrastructure/components/layout/StaticPageLayout.astro";
import { SiteConfig } from "@/app/config/site.config";
import { Path } from "@/app/config/path.config";
import NewsletterForm from "@/infrastructure/components/newsletter/NewsletterForm.astro";
import AuthorCard from "@/infrastructure/author/AuthorCard.astro";
---

<StaticPageLayout
  title="About Ravoid"
  description="Uncomfortable truths about SaaS infrastructure, AI agents in production, and the real cost of scaling."
>
  <!-- Menambahkan class 'prose' (Tailwind Typography) jika belum di-handle oleh layout -->
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Ravoid delivers sharp, no-fluff insights for engineering leaders and
      technical founders building serious SaaS and AI systems in production.
    </p>

    <p class="leading-relaxed">
      We cut through the hype around AI agent frameworks, infrastructure
      choices, and cost models. Most decisions that feel obviously correct in
      the early stage quietly become expensive, or outright risky, once you hit
      real usage and scale.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      Why Ravoid Exists
    </h2>

    <p class="leading-relaxed">
      Too many teams waste months and six-figure budgets on “flexible” agent
      frameworks, multi-cloud setups, or token pricing models that collapse
      under pressure. Ravoid exists to show the uncomfortable trade-offs before
      you pay the price.
    </p>

    <p class="leading-relaxed">
      Every article here is built on real production experience, realistic cost
      numbers, concrete scenarios across early, growth, and scale stages,
      meaningful trade-off tables, and decision frameworks that actually help
      you choose what survives scaling.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      What You’ll Get
    </h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
      <li>
        <strong>Opinionated breakdowns</strong> of AI agent frameworks in production,
        why most never escape pilot and what actually matters at scale.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Deep infrastructure analysis:</strong> serverless vs traditional,
        single vendor vs multi-cloud, and the hidden costs engineers only discover
        after it’s too late.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Realistic AI cost modeling</strong> and token economics, because “cheap
        at small volume” almost never stays cheap.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Stage-specific guidance</strong> and practical mental models so you
        stop guessing and start making defensible technical decisions.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      Behind Ravoid
    </h2>

    <AuthorCard />

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      Join the Readers Who Want the Truth
    </h2>

    <p class="leading-relaxed">
      If you’re responsible for systems that must stay reliable and
      cost-effective as they grow, Ravoid is built for you. Subscribe for sharp
      insights delivered directly—no fluff, no weekly tool roundups, just the
      hard-earned truths that matter when you’re in the trenches of production.
    </p>

    <!-- Placeholder untuk Tombol / Komponen Newsletter -->
    <div class="mt-4 mb-8">
      <NewsletterForm />
    </div>

    <hr
      class="my-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-200 to-transparent dark:from-white/10 dark:to-transparent"
    />

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
      Contact
    </h2>
    <p class="leading-relaxed">
      Have feedback, a war story, or a specific decision you want challenged?
      Reach out via the <a
        href={Path.contact}
        class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">contact page</a
      > or connect on <a
        href="https://linkedin.com/in/fradotech"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">LinkedIn</a
      >.
    </p>
  </div>
</StaticPageLayout>
